#   CODE-009: beagle: abc buffer ctor + one uri-resolver

beagle builds static Bu8/u8b buffers as {s,s,s,s+sizeof} literals with raw pointer arithmetic at six BE.cli.c + two DISPATCH.c sites, and BEActPromoteRef/BEActResolveRemote/BEActResolveRef share the same 'static scratch + loop over c->uris' shape. Use the abc buffer constructor and factor the uri-resolver loop.

##  Issues

Hand-rolled static buffer literals (ptr-arith) and a triplicated uri-resolve loop.

 -  Six BE.cli.c + two DISPATCH.c static Bu8 literals {st,st,st,st+sizeof} — CLAUDE.md §10 ptr-arith.
 -  BEActPromoteRef/BEActResolveRemote (DISPATCH.c:88,147) + BEActResolveRef (BE.cli.c:3287) share the uri-loop shape.

##  Blockers

None; shares BE.cli.c with CODE-008 — same beagle worktree, serial.

##  Planned

Replace literals with the abc buffer macro; factor one uri-resolve helper.

 -  Repro first (§17): be resolve/promote paths stay green.
 -  a_pad / abc buffer ctor for every scratch buf; drop the +sizeof literals.
 -  One BEResolveOverUris(c,fn) the three actors call.

